step.context:
\text{If $ A = [a_{ij}]_{m \times n}$ and } B = [b_{ij}]_{m \times n} 
\text{ are any two matrices,}\\
\text{then, are all the following conclusions correct?}

\text{What is the result of the following matrix}\\
\text{addition, }
2  
\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 3 \\ 
 0 & x \end{array} \right] + 

\left[\begin{array}{cc}
 y & 0 \\ 
 1 & 2 \end{array} \right] ?

step.tex:
\begin{align}
(2+y)+6+1+(2x+2) &= 5+6+1+8 \\
\implies 2x + y  &= 9
\end{align}\\
\text{So, the solutions of above linear equality give}\\
\text{the desired values of x and y.}
